<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-16T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-16T11:29:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1301</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-16T11:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1917—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Guzman, member of Congress, prominent in 1906 revolution,
                            political companion Ferrara, and active inciting present troubles,
                            surrendered today. He took the field at outbreak of revolution, but lost
                            all followers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>